We recommended that the Management require the Bids and Awards Committee to undertake the following:
Require the BAC-Inspectorate and the PhilGEPS Coordinator to refund the honoraria they received totaling P38,000.00, which they are not entitled to;
Compute the appropriate amount of BAC honoraria by multiplying the rate and the number of successfully completed procurement;
Grant BAC honoraria only to the individuals identified by the aforementioned Budget Circular, who actively participated in or were involved in the procurement activities; and
Ensure compliance with the relevant provisions of DBM Budget Circular No. 2004-5A in the granting of honoraria to the BAC.
Moreover, we recommended that the Members of the Bids and Awards Committee, the Technical Working Group and the BAC Secretariat perform their respective functions in accordance with Sections 12 and 14 of the Revised Implementing Rules and Regulations of RA No. 9184.

We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor require:

a. 	The Municipal Treasurer, in coordination with the Municipal Assessor, to prepare and furnish the Municipal Accountant a duly certified list of taxpayers showing the names and the amounts due and collectible based on updated Real Property Tax Account Register/Taxpayer’s Index Card to provide an accurate and reliable basis in setting up the Receivables from RPT and SET;

b. 	The Municipal Accountant to draw a Journal Entry Voucher to record the RPT/SET Receivables established at the beginning of the year based on the submitted duly certified list of taxpayers with the amount due and collectible for the year and maintain the corresponding subsidiary ledgers to monitor tax collections and delinquencies;

c. 	The Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to reconcile the RPT Receivable and SET Receivable set up at the beginning of the year and draw the appropriate adjusting entries, if necessary;

d. 	The Municipal Treasury to implement a more intensive strategy in the collection of Real Property Tax in the Municipality; and 

e. 	The concerned officials to adhere strictly to the provisions of Section 246 of RA No. 7160 and New Government Accounting System Manual for LGUs, Volume I.

