To fairly present the book value of the Road Networks account in the Financial Statements of the Municipality, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:

GSO and the Municipal Engineer to conduct the physical inventory on the Local Road Network to come up with the Inventory Report on the Local Road Network.

GSO and the Municipal Engineer to evaluate the Local Road Inventory Report and reconcile with the accounting records to facilitate the reporting of the municipality’s road network system;

Municipal Accountant to adjust the books on discrepancies noted;

Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO-Designate with the complete description and cost segregation of the road components for road project.

We recommended that Management require the Municipal Accountant to:

Issue demand letters to notify the concerned officials and employees who have long outstanding cash advances of their responsibility to settle the same. If settlement was not received within a reasonable period, withhold from their salaries and other benefits with due notice considering that they have been notified and given adequate time to voluntarily liquidate;

Refrain from providing additional cash advance to concerned officials and employees unless the previous cash advance granted to them have been liquidated;

Strictly comply with the provisions of the abovementioned Circulars to avoid the penalty stated therein.

