We reiterate our previous year’s audit recommendations that:

The Local Chief executive create an Inventory Committee to conduct the required physical inventory of all properties;

The General Services Officer prepare and submit to the auditor concerned the required Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) not later than January 31 of each year.

The Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer maintain Property Ledger Cards and;

The Municipal Accountant reconcile the RPCPPE with the accounting records.

We recommended to management the following:

Require the members of the SB to fully refund the amount of overpayment of P837,000.00that was not deducted from their RATA due to absences and non-conduct of the required four sessions in a month;Instruct the Municipal accounting Office to deduct from the RATA claims of the SB members pro-rated amounts based on actual work/attendance in regular sessions;

Support claims for RATA with SB minutes of meetings and certification of attendance from the SB secretary; 

Require the SB members to accomplish application  for leave  for recording in leave cards; and

Strictly comply with the requirements of Section 52 of RA. No. 7160 on the conduct of at least one regular session a week.
